# intraday-research env vars
# Copy to .env.intraday (gitignored) and fill in.

# --- Runner ---
INTRADAY_ADAPTER=mock              # mock | demo | kite | upstox | dhan
# INTRADAY_REPO_DIR=/absolute/path/to/repo
# INTRADAY_WATCHLIST=agents/config/watchlist.json
# INTRADAY_THRESHOLDS=agents/config/thresholds.json
# INTRADAY_OUT_DIR=$INTRADAY_REPO_DIR/out

# --- Broker credentials (fill only the one you use) ---

# Zerodha Kite Connect (access token rotates daily)
# KITE_API_KEY=
# KITE_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# Upstox
# UPSTOX_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# Dhan HQ — v2 API (fully wired, see agents/adapters/dhan.ts)
#
# Setup:
#   1. Log into https://web.dhan.co
#   2. Profile → DhanHQ Trading APIs
#   3. Note your Client ID (10-digit number near the top)
#   4. Click "Generate Access Token" — copy the JWT string
#   5. Ensure "Data API" is ENABLED on the same page (LTP / quote / charts
#      / option chain need this). If not enabled, quote calls return 403.
#   6. Fill both vars below. Token is typically 24h — regenerate daily.
#   7. Verify: bash scripts/dhan-verify.sh
#      (Expected: "✓ India VIX = <number>")
#   8. Run pipeline: INTRADAY_ADAPTER=dhan bash scripts/run-intraday-research.sh
#
# Security:
#   - This file (.env.intraday) is in .gitignore — never commit it.
#   - Never paste the token into chat, email, or any remote log.
#   - If a token leaks, revoke immediately at the same Dhan page.
#
# DHAN_CLIENT_ID=2603219806
# DHAN_ACCESS_TOKEN=eyJhbGciOiJIUzUxMi...

# --- Telegram push ---
# 1. Message @BotFather on Telegram, /newbot, save token here
# 2. Start a chat with your bot, then hit:
#    https://api.telegram.org/bot<TOKEN>/getUpdates
#    to find your chat id. For groups, add the bot and grab the negative id.
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=

# --- ntfy.sh push (optional, free, no account) ---
# Pick any hard-to-guess topic name.
# INTRADAY_NTFY_TOPIC=my-private-intraday-topic-abc123
